### Abstract
 
This paper documents an audio deepfake detection system built by fine-tuning the wav2vec2-large-xlsr-53 model on the ASVspoof2019 dataset. The system classifies audio as real or AI-generated with 92.86% accuracy and 4.01% Equal Error Rate. A Streamlit web interface is provided for interactive use.
 
---
 
### 1. Introduction
 
AI voice synthesis tools have made it easy to generate convincing fake audio. This creates risks in identity verification, misinformation, and biometric security. This project addresses that by fine-tuning a pretrained speech transformer for binary deepfake audio classification.
 
---
 
### 2. Dataset
 
**ASVspoof2019** contains:
- Real (bonafide) human speech recordings
- Spoofed audio generated by 19 different TTS and voice conversion systems
The evaluation subset was used for final benchmarking.
 
---
 
### 3. Model
 
**Base:** `https://huggingface.co/OBITO03/Deepfakewav2vec2` — a self-supervised speech model by Meta AI, pretrained on 53 languages (~56,000 hours of audio).
 
The model was originally fine-tuned on LibriSpeech for gender classification. This project fine-tunes it further on ASVspoof2019 for deepfake detection.
 
**Pipeline:**
- Input: raw audio waveform at 16kHz
- Feature extraction: 7-layer convolutional encoder
- Contextual representation: 24-layer transformer encoder
- Output: linear classifier → real / fake
---
 
### 4. Training Setup
 
| Parameter | Value |
|---|---|
| Base model | wav2vec2-large-xlsr-53 |
| Dataset | ASVspoof2019 |
| Classes | real, fake |
| Sampling rate | 16,000 Hz |
| Framework | HuggingFace Transformers |
| Weights file | model.safetensors (1.3GB) |
 
